title: Nutram I12 Ideal Solution Support Weight Control
descriptions: When evaluating a cat food, the first five ingredients can tell you a lot about the quality of a product as they make up the bulk of the product. Ideally, you're looking for quality protein sources with a minimum of cheap starches, fillers or by-products. Continuing down the ingredient list, look for ingredients that resemble real food with a minimal number of unpronounceable chemicals - the same as you would for human food.
key_benefits: less protein than average more carbohydrates than average significantly more fat than average less fiber than average
calorie: Using the calculations provided by the AAFCO, Nutram I12 Ideal Solution Support Weight Control has approximately 104 calories per 100g (29 calories/ounce), which is a few more calories compared to the average of the other wet cat foods in the CatFoodDB.
